                            <comment id="110413" author="adilger" created="Mon, 23 Mar 2015 19:03:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this has been around since &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2059&quot; title=&quot;mgc to backup configuration on osd-based llogs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2059&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2059&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &quot;llog: MGC to use OSD API for backup logs&quot; patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5049&lt;/a&gt; that was landed as v2_4_52_0-16-g3e38436.  This may cause random memory corruption for &lt;tt&gt;logname % 4 == 3&lt;/tt&gt; or maybe &lt;tt&gt;logname % 8 == 7&lt;/tt&gt; when the trailing NUL overflows the allocated buffer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
